"Los Angeles\", \"from\": 307, \"to\": 318}, {\"ngram\": \"bookmarks\", \"from\": 346, \"to\": 355}, {\"ngram\": \"offers\", \"from\": 389, \"to\": 395}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 397, \"to\": 403}, {\"ngram\": \"updates\", \"from\": 408, \"to\": 415}, {\"ngram\": \"The Independent\", \"from\": 421, \"to\": 436}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice All the travel books will tell you to avoid Paris in August - it's too crowded, too hot and everything is shut.\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 577, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 510, \"end\": 515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.138928345551497e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ourPrivacy notice\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 464}, {\"ngram\": \"All the travel books\", \"from\": 465, \"to\": 485}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 518, \"to\": 524}, {\"ngram\": \"everything\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 567}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Well, perhaps, these last two weeks have taught us to forget all those stereotypes about the French, with their smiling waiters, reliable public transport and cooling rain.\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 751, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 672, \"end\": 678, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9991296687638765, \"rank\": 0.000779109260269467, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these last two weeks\", \"from\": 594, \"to\": 614}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 629}, {\"ngram\": \"all those stereotypes\", \"from\": 640, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"their smiling waiters\", \"from\": 685, \"to\": 706}, {\"ngram\": \"reliable public transport\", \"from\": 708, \"to\": 733}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 746, \"to\": 750}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And as for their great summer tradition of strikes and riots, unfortunately that moved a little closer to home.\", \"from\": 753, \"to\": 864, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"their great summer tradition\", \"from\": 764, \"to\": 792}, {\"ngram\": \"strikes\", \"from\": 796, \"to\": 803}, {\"ngram\": \"riots\", \"from\": 808, \"to\": 813}, {\"ngram\": \"home\", \"from\": 859, \"to\": 863}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Whisper it quietly but Paris saw London 2012 and raised it, bringing theOlympicsto the heart of the world's most Instagrammable city.\", \"from\": 866, \"to\": 999, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 889, \"end\": 894, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.138928345551497e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 899, \"end\": 910, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.619664227997668e-13, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"theOlympicsto\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 948}, {\"ngram\": \"the heart\", \"from\": 949, \"to\": 958}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's most Instagrammable city\", \"from\": 962, \"to\": 998}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wherever you hopped off the Metro a viral moment was just a short walk away.\", \"from\": 1000, \"to\": 1076, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Metro\", \"from\": 1024, \"to\": 1033}, {\"ngram\": \"a viral moment\", \"from\": 1034, \"to\": 1048}, {\"ngram\": \"just a short walk\", \"from\": 1053, \"to\": 1070}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their opening ceremony left a little to be desired.\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1129, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their opening ceremony\", \"from\": 1078, \"to\": 1100}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You had to respect the ambition but four hours of interpretive dance, staged in pouring rain, could not even be saved by a spectacular light show and Celine Dion.\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1292, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1280, \"end\": 1291, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.6970596369718993e-51, \"text\": \"Celine Dion\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Celine_Dion\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the ambition\", \"from\": 1149, \"to\": 1161}, {\"ngram\": \"four hours\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1176}, {\"ngram\": \"interpretive dance\", \"from\": 1180, \"to\": 1198}, {\"ngram\": \"rain\", \"from\": 1218, \"to\": 1222}, {\"ngram\": \"a spectacular light show\", \"from\": 1251, \"to\": 1275}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But after the storm, came the sun, the sport and Snoop Dogg.\", \"from\": 1294, \"to\": 1354, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1343, \"end\": 1353, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Snoop Dogg\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Snoop_Dogg\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the storm\", \"from\": 1304, \"to\": 1313}, {\"ngram\": \"the sun\", \"from\": 1320, \"to\": 1327}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They say you are never far from the Eiffel Tower in Paris and Snoop lurked everywhere too.\", \"from\": 1355, \"to\": 1445, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1407, \"end\": 1412, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.138928345551497e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1387, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"Snoop\", \"from\": 1417, \"to\": 1422}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Their closing night show played it a little more safe and a touch too melancholy, Olympic officials making it privately clear there were unhappy with some ofthe more risque elements of Thomas Jolly's sodden opening night.\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1668, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1632, \"end\": 1638, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"score\": 0.8220214440455897, \"rank\": 0.20833427811569105, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_Wayne\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Their closing night show\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1471}, {\"ngram\": \"a touch\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1512}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic officials\", \"from\": 1529, \"to\": 1546}, {\"ngram\": \"some ofthe more risque elements\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1628}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes were honoured, volunteers were thanked, President Macron even got a small cheer, though if Leon Marchand wants to run for office, he'd win in a landslide, helping extinguish the flame at the Jardin des Tuileries.\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1891, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1719, \"end\": 1735, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"President Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}, {\"begin\": 1775, \"end\": 1783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"score\": 0.9907178779360891, \"rank\": 0.009333068560118132, \"text\": \"Marchand\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q11774891\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brad_Marchand\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 1670, \"to\": 1678}, {\"ngram\": \"volunteers\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1704}, {\"ngram\": \"a small cheer\", \"from\": 1745, \"to\": 1758}, {\"ngram\": \"office\", \"from\": 1801, \"to\": 1807}, {\"ngram\": \"a landslide\", \"from\": 1821, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"the flame\", \"from\": 1853, \"to\": 1862}, {\"ngram\": \"the Jardin des Tuileries\", \"from\": 1866, \"to\": 1890}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris, that city of die-hard romantics, seems a rather fitting place to fall back in love with the Olympics, 12 years after London wrote their blueprint for success.\", \"from\": 1893, \"to\": 2058, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1898, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.138928345551497e-23, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2017, \"end\": 2023, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999968168, \"rank\": 3.205845231059828e-12, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that city\", \"from\": 1900, \"to\": 1909}, {\"ngram\": \"die-hard romantics\", \"from\": 1913, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"a rather fitting place\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1961}, {\"ngram\": \"love\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 1982}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1988, \"to\": 2000}, {\"ngram\": \"their blueprint\", \"from\": 2030, \"to\": 2045}, {\"ngram\": \"success\", \"from\": 2050, \"to\": 2057}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have been relentlessly worrying about this fortnight here for seven years but they have been just what Macron needed, a temporary truce on the political divisiveness that remains his most pressing problem.\", \"from\": 2060, \"to\": 2270, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2168, \"end\": 2174, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 0.99999999931606, \"rank\": 6.838494438490334e-10, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"this fortnight\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2117}, {\"ngram\": \"seven years\", \"from\": 2127, \"to\": 2138}, {\"ngram\": \"a temporary truce\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"the political divisiveness\", \"from\": 2204, \"to\": 2230}, {\"ngram\": \"his most pressing problem\", \"from\": 2244, \"to\": 2269}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jacques Chirac's popularity peaked after France won the World Cup, Macron's motorcade often swept into venues from the Elysees Palace just moments before another gold was won.\", \"from\": 2272, \"to\": 2447, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2272, \"end\": 2286, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jacques Chirac\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jacques_Chirac\"}, {\"begin\": 2313, \"end\": 2319, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999582232972094, \"rank\": 3.965854282975583e-05, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 2339, \"end\": 2345, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"score\": 0.99999999931606, \"rank\": 6.838494438490334e-10, \"text\": \"Macron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Emmanuel_Macron\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the World Cup\", \"from\": 2324, \"to\": 2337}, {\"ngram\": \"venues\", \"from\": 2375, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"the Elysees Palace\", \"from\": 2387, \"to\": 2405}, {\"ngram\": \"another gold\", \"from\": 2426, \"to\": 2438}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The reported cost of this two-week circus, remember the Paralympics are still to come, was \\u00a37.8 billion, the 'cheapest' summer Games in two decades.\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2597, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The reported cost\", \"from\": 2449, \"to\": 2466}, {\"ngram\": \"this two-week circus\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2490}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paralympics\", \"from\": 2501, \"to\": 2516}, {\"ngram\": \"the 'cheapest' summer Games\", \"from\": 2554, \"to\": 2581}, {\"ngram\": \"two decades\", \"from\": 2585, \"to\": 2596}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The biggest single cost was security, you were never far from a gendarmerie with a gun.\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2685, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The biggest single cost\", \"from\": 2598, \"to\": 2621}, {\"ngram\": \"security\", \"from\": 2626, \"to\": 2634}, {\"ngram\": \"a gendarmerie\", \"from\": 2660, \"to\": 2673}, {\"ngram\": \"a gun\", \"from\": 2679, \"to\": 2684}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As ever the challenges comes with what's next.\", \"from\": 2687, \"to\": 2733, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the challenges\", \"from\": 2695, \"to\": 2709}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Team GB - fuelled by crucial National Lottery investment - bucked a trend by winning more medals in the Games post-hosting in Rio but that's no easy task for the French, who enjoyed their best medal return for 124 years.\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2954, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2860, \"end\": 2863, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999984521780945, \"rank\": 1.5478243323565898e-06, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.